Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Fredinard Darnell Jackson in court without counsel, in custody.  Michael R Staskunas appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Fredinard Darnell Jackson appeared by video means.
Case in court for return on warrant.  Defendant appears in Court without counsel.  Defendant is not eligible for public defender representation.  Defendant requests court appointed counsel at the county rate.  Court appoints Attorney Morgan L. Minter who shall be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. Court orders defendant to repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning January 1, 2023 and every month thereafter until paid in full.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  Court hears arguments as to bail.  For reasons as set forth on the record, Court set bail at $100.00 with Justice Point Supervision LEVEL 3.  Court ordered case adjourned for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Bench Warrant Cleared by Milwaukee County Sheriff.  Original (Copy) bench warrant received.  Case calendared for Return on Warrant August 19, 2022 at 8:30 am.
Notice of bond forfeiture mailed to defendant. ($2,000.00 signature bond) LW
Signature bond ordered to be forfeited in the amount of 2000.00.
